## 🗒️ Architecture Notes
- `employment_status` on `network_member_roles` — NOT `profiles`
- `location_ids` on `network_member_roles`: null/empty = all locations
- `hourly_rate` and `holiday_allowance` on `network_member_roles`
- `isPremiumProfile()` in `lib/supabase.ts` — single source of truth for tier checks
- All dashboard fetches use `locationRef.current` (useRef) to avoid stale closures
- `team_members` table is legacy — ignore it, use `network_member_roles` exclusively
- `clockedInMembers` fetched in `dashboard.tsx`, passed as prop — components never query `time_entries` directly
- Daily reports → `reports` table, `type: 'daily'`, full data in `data` JSONB column
- Currency from `locations.currency_symbol` / `locations.currency_code` — never hardcoded
- Workflows are user-scoped — `fetchWorkflows` never filters by location; display filtering at render time only
- `inventory_items` are owner-scoped; quantities per-location in `location_inventory`
- Upsert `location_inventory` on unique `(location_id, inventory_item_id)`
- Invoice images in Supabase Storage bucket `order-scans`, RLS: owner reads/writes own files
- Invoice parser and recipe parser are completely separate Claude API calls — different prompts, different files
- `EnvironmentalReportScreen` accepts `editId` param for in-place editing of SoD reports
- `reports.ts` exports `updateEnvironmentalReport(id, updates)` and `updateDailyReport(id, updates)`
- Equipment temps (`fridgeTemp`, `freezerTemp`, `proofTemp`, `ovenTemp`) on `environmental_reports` — DB migration required before deploying new SoD screen
- `fetchInventoryParSnapshot(userId, locationId?)` in `reports.ts` — called at EoD generation time
- POS tokens encrypted with AES-256-GCM before DB insertion — key in `POS_ENCRYPTION_KEY` env var
- `sync-pos` edge function uses Deno Web Crypto (self-contained) — does NOT import from website lib
- `getUserFromRequest(req)` in `lib/supabase.ts` — reads Bearer token, verifies via `auth.getUser()`
- `createAuthenticatedClient(token)` in `lib/supabase.ts` — user-scoped client that respects RLS
- POS OAuth providers: Square (live), Lightspeed Retail (live), Clover (pending), Toast (deferred)
- `pages/connections.tsx` — standalone page for POS connect/disconnect, accessible from dashboard hamburger menu